President Cyril Ramaphosa. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa says discussions need to be had about what's hindering the growth and progress of black businesses in South Africa. He adds that non-payment issues by government to businesses also needs to be solved. Ramaphosa opened the Black Industrialist Conference.  President Cyril Ramaphosa says black businesses can't grow when there's power cuts. Ramaphosa says rolling blackouts need to be dealt with urgently. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/lheDBxU0Wq